COSMOS FS2′ (docs/COSMOS-FACET-SEAMS-V2.md §2) — the FP_DATUM_BAKE near-mesh hook.

Applies AFTER 0008 (glob order), on the fully-patched VoxelMesherBlocky. Adds set_facet_datum_bake(Dictionary)
+ the FacetDatumBakeParams blob + a per-vertex build()-time lift: every near-mesh vertex is raised by the
CONTINUOUS per-column datum s = -b + sqrt(b^2 + R^2 - |p0|^2) along the facet-lattice up axis (local +Y), so the
flat-lattice near field renders at the radial surface R+s while the voxel CONTENT stays byte-identical (positions
only, no re-index, NO generator change). facet_datum_lift mirrors FacetAtlas.datum_lift EXACTLY from the already-
frozen atlas frame row (o/du/dv/nhat + off + R). enabled=false (or an empty dict / an unpatched binary via the
has_method guard) => the plain flat mesher, byte-identical to the pre-FS2' engine. This REPLACES the retired FS2
generator patch (0009, removed): the generator is untouched. Kept as a standalone patch so the hunk offsets are
git-generated and cannot drift against the earlier mesher patches (0003 near-bake, 0004 facet-carve).

